Now let us move toStudentRepo and StaffRepo classes; they seem very similar, to remove this redundancy we want to replace them  with a single PersonRepo class that can hold Student or Staff items (i.e. an instance of PersonRepo can hold either Student or St aff instances) in a type safe way. Provide an implementation for such a PersonRepoclass. 
public class PersonRepo{
PersonRepo(String type){
  if(type.equals("Student")){
    protected List<Student> students = new ArrayList<>(); 
  }
  else if(type.equals("Staff")){
    protected List<Staff> staffs = new ArrayList<>(); 
  }
}
}


public class StudentRepo extends PersonRepo { 
 
 public void addStudent(Student s){ 
 students.add(s); 
 }


public class StaffRepo extends PersonRepo{ 
 public void addStaff(Staff s){ 
 staffs.add(s); 
 } 
